    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "A number of saloons situated\nwithin the boundaries of the Nez\nPerez Indian reservation in Idaho\nhave been put out of business by a\nrecent decision of the U. S. SUI\npreme court. The ruling affirms\na sentence of Imprisonment against\nan Indian for selling liquor pro-\ncured from white men to other In\ndians. The NeZ Perez treaty pro-\nvides that no liquor shall ever be\nsold on the reservation. Saloons\nhave been started in towns in the\nreservation lines and about 35 of\nthese will be closed."
    }
  ]
